    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** lineup for 2026-04-30 is anchored by **Gunnar Henderson**, who registers as our top play with a massive 83.29 efficiency score. Facing McCullers Jr. in a favorable park, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a 16% park adjustment and a 19% SP skill edge, while his elite sprint speed is further weaponized by the opposing pitcher's slow delivery, creating a high-ceiling environment for stolen base opportunities. Joining him at the top of the lineup, **Jacob Wilson** (74.08) holds the second-highest score of the day, leveraging a prime leadoff spot against the left-handed Cameron. Both **Gunnar Henderson** and **Jacob Wilson** are essential today, as their projected production\u2014boosted significantly by their batting order and favorable platoon splits\u2014is critical for overcoming the inherent scarcity of SB points in our 5x5 format.\n\nRounding out the core, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (71.02) provides the safest floor in the middle of the order, benefiting from Ober's 4.51 xERA and a strong xwOBA profile that offsets the slight penalty for being a righty against an RHP. While **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (60.56) earns a \"Strong\" start due to a 14% platoon adjustment, we are exercising caution with **Nasim Nunez** (47.72) and **Drake Baldwin** (54.14). **Nasim Nunez** is a high-upside play for steals due to the opposing catcher\u2019s 1.87s pop time, but his marginal score reflects the difficulty of facing Peralta. We remain sidelined on key contributors like **Kyle Tucker**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Andy Pages**, and **Jackson Merrill**, all of whom are unavailable today due to schedule gaps or injury, leaving our depth\u2014including players like **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Josh Lowe**\u2014ready to step in should we need to manage our game caps moving forward. No significant weather hazards were identified for today's slate, though the efficiency of **Drake Baldwin** remains tied to his confirmed lineup placement; any move down the order would likely relegate him to the bench.",
